# 🔒 API Security Testing Lab

## Overview

This repository documents my hands-on API security testing journey using [OWASP crAPI](https://owasp.org/www-project-crapi/) (Completely Ridiculous API), a deliberately vulnerable API application that demonstrates the OWASP API Security Top 10 vulnerabilities.

**Goal:** Identify, exploit, and document real API vulnerabilities in a safe, legal environment while building a portfolio that demonstrates practical API security skills.

---

## 📋 Lab Setup

### Prerequisites
- Docker & Docker Compose
- Burp Suite / OWASP ZAP
- Postman (optional)

### Quick Start

```bash
# Clone this repository
git clone https://github.com/MuizRecon/api-security-testing-lab.git
cd api-security-testing-lab

# Download crAPI
curl -o docker-compose.yml https://raw.githubusercontent.com/OWASP/crAPI/main/deploy/docker/docker-compose.yml

# Start the lab
docker compose -f docker-compose.yml --compatibility up -d
Access Points
Service	URL
Main Application	http://localhost:8888
Mail Server (Mailhog)	http://localhost:8025
🔍 Methodology
For each vulnerability, I follow a structured approach:

Discovery - Identify the endpoint and understand intended behavior

Exploitation - Craft requests to demonstrate the vulnerability

Documentation - Capture evidence with screenshots and detailed steps

Remediation - Research and propose fixes with code examples

